    "updated_at": "2017-02-27T15:23:47Z",
    "body": "I guess you may not register the shortcuts. By default electron.app will do this for you, \r\nunless you do cover the default menu. Then you need to register these shortcuts by yourself.\r\n\r\nThe api is here http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/global-shortcut/\r\n\r\nMake some mistakes, but the way is the same. Electron.app may not register the \"alt+r\"\r\nfor you. So you need to do it by yourself. \r\n\r\nYou can [get the webContents of the devtool](http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/web-contents/#contentsdevtoolswebcontents), and use [the reload function](http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/web-contents/#contentsreload), and register \r\nthe function to a shortcut."
